    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">King Ferdinand I to Pál Várday and Miklós Oláh (Wiener Neustadt,
                    19 September 1548)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">They will understand from the attached petition from the
                            county of Sopron why Nádasdy rejected Ferenc Soós as commissioner in the
                            feud between Nádasdy and the Sopron county. And although the county
                            wants to replace Soós with Hans von Weispriach, <hi rend="italic"
                                >ispán</hi> of Sopron county, according to King Ferdinand I, it is
                            no coincidence that Nádasdy objects to reinstating such a suspicious
                            person as head of the county. He wants this feud to end and charges them
                            (Várday and Oláh) with finding a worthy and suitable person to replace
                            Soós, so that the commissioners can already make a report at the next
                            Bratislava assembly.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Ferdinandus.<note xml:id="note.1">there is a comment on the margin:
                        “ponetur titulus”.</note></p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Ex supplicatione comitatus Soproniensis <add corresp="scriba"
                        type="insert">hisce adiecta</add> Fidelitas Vestra abunde intelliget, quod
                    spectabilis et magnificus fidelis nobis dilectus <persName>Thomas de
                        Nadasd</persName> etc. <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">acceptare</add>
                    recusaverit et repudiarit egregium fidelem nobis dilectum <del corresp="scriba"
                        >Simonem</del><persName><add corresp="scriba" type="corr">Franciscum</add>
                        Soss de Mykebuda</persName><note xml:id="note.2">Ferenc Soós of Mikebuda was
                        a retainer <hi rend="italic">(familiaris)</hi> and vidame <hi rend="italic"
                            >(praefectus)</hi> of the Széchy family in Sopron, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Koppány</hi> 2014, 227.</note> pro commissario in
                    controversiis inter dictum <persName>Nadasd</persName> et comitatum Soproniensem
                    versantibus. Et quamquam comitatus praedictus cuperet in locum ipsius
                        <persName>Soss</persName> comitem suum <persName>Iohannem a
                        Weisprach</persName><note xml:id="note.3">Hans von Weispriach or János
                        Weispriach was <hi rend="italic">ispán</hi> of Sopron county, Baron of
                        Kabold and owner of the castle in Landsee until 1548. For more on him and
                        his family, see <hi rend="smallcap">Csermelyi</hi> 2013; and <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Csermelyi</hi> 2021, 197–209.</note> substitui, nos
                    tamen existimamus, quod nihilo serius nec inmerito <add corresp="scriba"
                        type="insert">praefatus Nadasd</add> gravari, ipsumque a
                        <persName>Weisprach</persName> tamquam personam suspectam, <add
                        corresp="scriba" type="insert">cum nimirum comes sit illius comitatus</add>,
                    reiicere posset. Idcirco nos cupientes huiusmodi controversias primo quoque
                    tempore sopitas atque sublatas esse pro <del corresp="scriba">ea paterna animi
                        nostri benevolentia</del> paterno animo nostro et benevolentia, qua fideles
                    subditos nostros prosequi solemus, Fidelitati Vestrae mandamus, quod in locum
                    praefati <persName>Francisci Soss</persName> aliquam aliam idoneam et aptam, nec
                    suspectam personam <del corresp="scriba">deligatis</del><add corresp="scriba"
                        type="corr">deligere</add> ac reliquis duobus commissariis ad memoratum
                    negotium deputatis adiungere velint, ita ut huiusmodi commissio <del
                        corresp="scriba">quamprimum fierit poterit</del><add corresp="scriba"
                        type="corr">citra omnem moram et ea quidem celeritate</add> debitum et
                    optatum effectum consequatur, <del corresp="scriba">ita ut</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">ut</add> nos ad proxime futurum generalem
                    conventum Posoniensem<note xml:id="note.4">16 October, 1548, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Mikó</hi> 2017, 69–73.</note> per dictorum
                    commissariorum relationem <add corresp="scriba" type="insert">de statu eius
                        negotii</add> informati, postea in huiusmodi causa ulterius progredi atque
                    id quod necessitas ac status earum rerum postulaverit, ordinare, <del
                        corresp="scriba">ac</del> statuere et providere queamus. In <milestone
                        unit="pb"/>quibus <del corresp="scriba">devotiones</del><add
                        corresp="scriba" type="corr">Devotio</add> et Fidelitas Vestrae exsequentur
                    voluntatem nostram.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Datum in <placeName>Nova Civitate</placeName> 19. Septembris
                    1548.</p>
            </div>
